[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":410},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2021\u002F07\u002F13\u002Fcodesandbox-quick-start-guide\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2021\u002F07\u002F13\u002Fcodesandbox-quick-start-guide\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2021\u002F07\u002F13\u002Fcodesandbox-quick-start-guide\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2021\u002F07\u002F13\u002Fcodesandbox-quick-start-guide\u002F":385,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2021\u002F07\u002F13\u002Fcodesandbox-quick-start-guide\u002F":394},"\u002Fother\u002F20210713\u002F2942275876\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":367,"date":368,"description":369,"extension":370,"lang":371,"meta":372,"navigation":373,"path":374,"readingMinutes":375,"seo":376,"standalone":377,"stem":378,"tags":379,"tldr":382,"updated":382,"url":383,"__hash__":384},"content\u002Fen\u002FMisc\u002Fcodesandbox-quick-start-guide.md","CodeSandbox Quick Start (10-Minute Tour)","9422758762",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":357},"minimark",[11,16,25,29,35,41,44,50,53,57,68,74,77,99,102,105,111,115,118,124,127,133,140,146,149,152,166,170,179,185,188,194,201,207,210,216,219,224,227,232,236,239,245,248,262,265,268,280,284,287,293,300,306,312,335,338,341,345,353],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19,20,24],"p",{},"CodeSandbox is great — but very different from CodePen. Think of CodeSandbox as \"your local dev environment, online\". You can pick frameworks, run ",[21,22,23],"code",{},"npm install",", and use it for real project work. So CodeSandbox is basically a more advanced CodePen. This post walks through the basics.",[12,26,28],{"id":27},"codesandbox","CodeSandbox",[17,30,31],{},[32,33],"img",{"alt":28,"src":34},"https:\u002F\u002Fcamo.githubusercontent.com\u002F9035083a04bffa6ef072e20f6036c58da2174f18e5f5e130cec3d1323f0fec68\u002F68747470733a2f2f636f646573616e64626f782e696f2f7374617469632f696d672f62616e6e65722e706e673f763d32",[17,36,37,38,40],{},"CodeSandbox's name comes from \"sandbox\" — the security concept. A sandbox is an isolated environment for trying things out without affecting your real machine. CodeSandbox runs your code in that kind of isolated environment in the cloud — full project setups, including ",[21,39,23],{},".",[17,42,43],{},"If you use VSCode, CodeSandbox will feel immediately familiar — the UI is basically 87% VSCode.",[17,45,46],{},[32,47],{"alt":48,"src":49},"CodeSandbox UI","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002Fvideo-fe2b0a3ea133c28d5a99cfc0ed2313ff.jpg",[17,51,52],{},"It's also surprisingly powerful.",[12,54,56],{"id":55},"initial-setup","Initial setup",[17,58,59,60,67],{},"When you hit the ",[61,62,66],"a",{"href":63,"rel":64},"https:\u002F\u002Fcodesandbox.io\u002Fs\u002F",[65],"nofollow","new sandbox URL",", you pick the template:",[17,69,70],{},[32,71],{"alt":72,"src":73},"Template picker","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F202107132107.png",[17,75,76],{},"A few of the templates available:",[78,79,80,84,87,90,93,96],"ul",{},[81,82,83],"li",{},"React",[81,85,86],{},"Vanilla",[81,88,89],{},"Vue",[81,91,92],{},"Vue 3",[81,94,95],{},"Angular",[81,97,98],{},"static",[17,100,101],{},"(That's only a few — there are way more, including a Node HTTP Server template.)",[17,103,104],{},"Annotated UI for the picker (the screenshot was annotated in Chinese, but the layout is the same in English):",[17,106,107],{},[32,108],{"alt":109,"src":110},"Template picker annotations","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F202107132113.png",[12,112,114],{"id":113},"create-a-sandbox","Create a sandbox",[17,116,117],{},"Let's create a Vue 3 sandbox. Click Vue 3:",[17,119,120],{},[32,121],{"alt":122,"src":123},"Vue 3 template","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F202107132117.png",[17,125,126],{},"After it provisions the environment, you've got something that looks a lot like VSCode online:",[17,128,129],{},[32,130],{"alt":131,"src":132},"Sandbox UI","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202021-07-13%2021.18.41.png",[17,134,135,136,139],{},"CodeSandbox Vue 3 shows a ",[21,137,138],{},"yarn.lock"," but actually uses npm under the hood. Annotated UI for the editor:",[17,141,142],{},[32,143],{"alt":144,"src":145},"Editor annotations","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F202121340713.png",[17,147,148],{},"Many CodeSandbox features need login, and you can only create 3 sandboxes without an account. So sign in before going deeper. The rest of this post is on a logged-in account.",[17,150,151],{},"Here's the sandbox I created for reference:",[153,154],"iframe",{"src":155,"style":156,"title":157,"allow":158,"sandbox":159},"https:\u002F\u002Fcodesandbox.io\u002Fembed\u002Fpedantic-villani-li2uw?fontsize=14&hidenavigation=1&theme=dark","width:100%; height:500px; border:0; border-radius: 4px; overflow:hidden;","Vue Example1","accelerometer; ambient-light-sensor; camera; encrypted-media; geolocation; gyroscope; hid; microphone; midi; payment; usb; vr; xr-spatial-tracking",[160,161,162,163,164,165],"allow-forms","allow-modals","allow-popups","allow-presentation","allow-same-origin","allow-scripts",[12,167,169],{"id":168},"installing-packages","Installing packages",[17,171,172,173,178],{},"How do you install packages in a sandbox? Say I want ",[61,174,177],{"href":175,"rel":176},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.npmjs.com\u002Fpackage\u002Fvue-loading-overlay",[65],"vue-loading-overlay"," (a nice Vue loading overlay package). Search \"vue-loading-overlay\" in the \"Dependencies\" panel:",[17,180,181],{},[32,182],{"alt":183,"src":184},"vue-loading-overlay search","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202021-07-13%2021.41.00.png",[17,186,187],{},"Click the top result and it installs:",[17,189,190],{},[32,191],{"alt":192,"src":193},"Installed","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202021-07-13%2021.41.49.png",[17,195,196,197,200],{},"To remove — hover over and click the ",[21,198,199],{},"X",":",[17,202,203],{},[32,204],{"alt":205,"src":206},"Remove package","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202021-07-13%2021.42.36.png",[17,208,209],{},"You can also click the dropdown to pick a specific version:",[17,211,212],{},[32,213],{"alt":214,"src":215},"Version selector","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202021-07-13%2021.43.22.png",[17,217,218],{},"Here's a working example with vue-loading-overlay installed:",[153,220],{"src":221,"style":156,"title":222,"allow":158,"sandbox":223},"https:\u002F\u002Fcodesandbox.io\u002Fembed\u002Fvue-example-vue-loading-overlay-tm528?fontsize=14&hidenavigation=1&theme=dark","Vue Example vue-loading-overlay",[160,161,162,163,164,165],[17,225,226],{},"And another template I prepared earlier:",[153,228],{"src":229,"style":156,"title":230,"allow":158,"sandbox":231},"https:\u002F\u002Fcodesandbox.io\u002Fembed\u002Fvue-simple-template-2dsiz?fontsize=14&hidenavigation=1&theme=dark","Vue Simple Template",[160,161,162,163,164,165],[12,233,235],{"id":234},"codesandbox-shortcuts","CodeSandbox shortcuts",[17,237,238],{},"CodeSandbox supports Emmet:",[17,240,241],{},[32,242],{"alt":243,"src":244},"Emmet","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202021-07-13%2021.56.24.png",[17,246,247],{},"Format shortcut:",[78,249,250,256],{},[81,251,252,253],{},"Mac: ",[21,254,255],{},"Shift + Option + F",[81,257,258,259],{},"Windows: ",[21,260,261],{},"Shift + Alt + F",[17,263,264],{},"(You usually don't need this — CodeSandbox auto-formats on save.)",[17,266,267],{},"Save shortcut:",[78,269,270,275],{},[81,271,252,272],{},[21,273,274],{},"Option + S",[81,276,258,277],{},[21,278,279],{},"Alt + S",[12,281,283],{"id":282},"exporting-your-code","Exporting your code",[17,285,286],{},"Another solid feature — export. If you've gotten a project to a state you like and want to keep working locally, just hit Export:",[17,288,289],{},[32,290],{"alt":291,"src":292},"Export","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202021-07-13%2022.08.51.png",[17,294,295,296,299],{},"The exported structure looks just like what ",[21,297,298],{},"vue-cli"," produces:",[17,301,302],{},[32,303],{"alt":304,"src":305},"Vue CLI layout","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202021-07-13%2022.09.59.png",[17,307,308,309,311],{},"Just unzip, ",[21,310,23],{},", and run:",[313,314,319],"pre",{"className":315,"code":316,"language":317,"meta":318,"style":318},"language-cmd shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","npm install\nnpm run serve\n","cmd","",[21,320,321,329],{"__ignoreMap":318},[322,323,326],"span",{"class":324,"line":325},"line",1,[322,327,328],{},"npm install\n",[322,330,332],{"class":324,"line":331},2,[322,333,334],{},"npm run serve\n",[17,336,337],{},"You're developing locally with zero scaffold work.",[17,339,340],{},"The one minor downside of CodeSandbox — compile feels a bit slow sometimes.",[12,342,344],{"id":343},"references","References",[78,346,347],{},[81,348,349],{},[61,350,28],{"href":351,"rel":352},"https:\u002F\u002Fcodesandbox.io",[65],[354,355,356],"style",{},"html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}",{"title":318,"searchDepth":331,"depth":331,"links":358},[359,360,361,362,363,364,365,366],{"id":14,"depth":331,"text":15},{"id":27,"depth":331,"text":28},{"id":55,"depth":331,"text":56},{"id":113,"depth":331,"text":114},{"id":168,"depth":331,"text":169},{"id":234,"depth":331,"text":235},{"id":282,"depth":331,"text":283},{"id":343,"depth":331,"text":344},"Misc","2021-07-13 20:51:14","CodeSandbox is genuinely great — and pretty different from CodePen. Where CodePen is \"online editor for snippets\", CodeSandbox is more like \"your local dev environment, in the cloud\" — full templates for React \u002F Vue \u002F Angular \u002F Node \u002F static, real npm install support, and a UI that's 87% VSCode. This post walks through the basics: creating a sandbox, installing packages, keyboard shortcuts, and exporting back to a local project.","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002Fcodesandbox-quick-start-guide","2",{"title":6,"description":369},false,"en\u002FMisc\u002Fcodesandbox-quick-start-guide",[28,380,381],"CodeSandbox Tutorial","CodeSandbox Basics",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2021\u002F07\u002F13\u002Fcodesandbox-quick-start-guide\u002F","lfTWS2IiD_7G1zN4kQRI_fT63Jjm22zdDfPrXdI5YJ0",{"newer":386,"older":390},{"url":387,"title":388,"date":389},"\u002Fen\u002Fpython\u002F2021\u002F07\u002F18\u002Fvscode-python3-venv-config\u002F","Setting Up Python 3 venv in VSCode","2021-07-18 12:26:51",{"url":391,"title":392,"date":393},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2021\u002F07\u002F12\u002Fjavascript-var-a-b-comma-operator\u002F","What Does var a, b = (1, 2) Actually Output? (And Why)","2021-07-12 11:44:56",[395,400,405],{"url":396,"title":397,"date":398,"readingMinutes":399},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F06\u002F23\u002Fmac-stats-menu-bar-system-monitor\u002F","Stats — The Free Open-Source macOS Menu Bar System Monitor I Use Every Day (CPU, GPU, Temperature, Network)","2026-06-23 10:00:00","5",{"url":401,"title":402,"date":403,"readingMinutes":404},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F05\u002F26\u002Fhow-much-does-a-blog-really-earn-with-google-adsense\u002F","Can a Blog Really Make Tens of Thousands of Dollars a Month? Real Google AdSense Numbers, Explained","2026-05-26 21:00:00","6",{"url":406,"title":407,"date":408,"readingMinutes":409},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F05\u002F18\u002Fvscode-disable-integrated-browser-auto-open\u002F","VSCode Opens Every Link in the Integrated Browser? How to Disable Auto Takeover","2026-05-18 14:30:00","4",1784020369307]